{{ Infobox Person | name = Dmitry Lomakov | nationality = Russian | occupation = Businessman and car collector }}
'''Dmitry Lomakov''' is a Russian businessman and car collector, the director of Moscow's museum of retro-automobiles.<ref name="theguardian1">{{cite news|author=Luke Harding |author2=Kate Connolly |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/nov/27/adolf-hitler-mercedes-war-trophy |title=Adolf Hitler's Mercedes, the ultimate war trophy for a Russian collector &#124; World news |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date= |accessdate=2016-05-06}}</ref>
Lomakov is the president of Retromoto, and owns 120 antique, including a Mercedes Benz owned by [[Adolf Hitler]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Sammy Said |url=http://www.therichest.com/rich-list/the-biggest/the-10-biggest-car-collectors-in-the-world/?view=all |title=The 10 Biggest Car Collectors In The World |publisher=TheRichest |date=2013-05-10 |accessdate=2016-05-06}}</ref> His collection includes [[Joseph Goebbels]]' [[Mercedes-Benz 540]]K, which was acquired by his father in 1972, [[Hermann Göring]]'s [[Horch|Horch 853]] limousine, and [[Martin Bormann]]'s [[Mercedes-Benz 320A]].<ref name="theguardian1"/>
According to Lomakov, Nazi cars are "symbols of Russia's victory".<ref name="theguardian1"/>
