{{BLP sources|date=September 2010}} {{Infobox person | image = | image_size = | name = Jonas af Jochnick | caption = | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1937}} | birth_place = [[Sweden]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Businessman }} '''Jonas af Jochnick''' (born 1937)<ref name=investors>{{Cite web |url=http://www.oriflame.com/en/investors/board/|title=Oriflame Investors Board}}</ref> is most notable for co-founding [[Oriflame]] Cosmetics with his brother [[Robert af Jochnick]] in 1967 in [[Sweden]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2008/11/23/fin12.asp|title=Oriflame group records 44% growth in Asia|date=23 November 2008|work=[[Sunday Observer]]|accessdate=21 September 2010}}</ref> In 2003 the brothers shared the [[International Swede of the Year]] award. As of 2006, Jonas af Jochnick was Sweden's 19th wealthiest person as estimated by business magazine [[Veckans Affärer]].
